{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_8","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' task-plans/codex-multi-agent-coordination-task-plan.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Codex Multi-Agent Coordination Task Plan\n\nStatus: active\n\n## Priority\n\nPriority 3\n\n## Objective\n\nSupport deliberate collaboration across multiple Codex threads.\n\n## Scope\n\n- multi-thread work planning\n- ownership and baton passing\n- coordination surfaces\n- team-state visibility\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Task 1 — Coordination Model\n\n- [ ] define how work is assigned between threads\n- [ ] define what counts as ownership, handoff, and waiting\n\n### Task 2 — Shared Coordination UI\n\n- [ ] expose multi-thread coordination state clearly\n- [ ] prevent coordination state from collapsing into the board visuals\n\n### Task 3 — Handoff Support\n\n- [ ] support explicit handoff cues\n- [ ] keep related threads linked as part of one larger work plan\n\n## Exit Criteria\n\n- multiple Codex threads can be used as a coordinated work set\n- coordination semantics are explicit, not implicit\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
